---
description: Modals must not close when clicking the backdrop
alwaysApply: true
---

# Modal dismissal

Never close a modal when the user clicks outside the panel (on the backdrop/overlay). Users must dismiss modals explicitly via a close button, Cancel, or another intentional control.

## Do not

- Attach `onClick={onClose}` or `onClick={onCancel}` to the backdrop wrapper
- Treat backdrop click as an implicit dismiss action

## Do

- Put `onClose` / `onCancel` only on explicit buttons (×, Cancel, Save & close, etc.)
- Use `role="presentation"` on the backdrop with no click handler
- Set `role="dialog"` (or `role="alertdialog"`) and `aria-modal="true"` on the panel

## Example

```jsx
// ❌ BAD — closes when clicking outside
<div className="fixed inset-0 ..." onClick={onClose}>
  <div onClick={(e) => e.stopPropagation()}>...</div>
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — only explicit controls close
<div className="fixed inset-0 ..." role="presentation">
  <div role="dialog" aria-modal="true">...</div>
</div>
```
